entries.title: NASA to test nuclear rocket engine for possible Mars missions
entries.description: A nuclear thermal rocket engine in development could one day transport humans to Mars.

entries.title: See emaciated shelter dog's incredible transformation
entries.description: In January 2021, Ethan Almighty was left for dead outside of the Kentucky Humane Society. Now, Gov. Beshear is honoring his fight by declaring January "Ethan Almighty Animal Shelter Awareness Month." CNN affiliate WLEX reports.

entries.title: Leopard 2 tanks would provide Kyiv with modern, powerful vehicle
entries.description: Germany is set to send its sought-after Leopard 2 tanks to Ukraine to help bolster the country's war effort, Der Spiegel reported on Tuesday evening, attributing to unnamed sources. German Chancellor Olaf Scholz has decided to deliver the battle tanks following "months of debate," according to the German news outlet's exclusive report.

entries.title: Decision comes after 'months of debate,' Der Spiegel report says. Parliament is still due to debate the issue
Kim Kardashian's Skims taps 'White Lotus' breakout stars for new campaign
entries.description: Scheming "White Lotus" besties Mia and Lucia have moved onto their next gig: a Skims fashion campaign.

entries.title: Justin Bieber sells his music catalog in $200 million deal
entries.description: Justin Bieber has sold the rights to his publishing and artist royalties from his song catalog, adding himself to a growing list of pop stars who have inked rights deals.

entries.title: Pritzker Prize-winning architect Balkrishna Doshi dies at age 95
entries.description: Balkrishna Doshi, one of the Indian subcontinent's most celebrated architects, has died at the age of 95.

entries.title: Classified documents found at Pence's Indiana home
entries.description: A lawyer for former Vice President Mike Pence discovered about a dozen documents marked as classified at Pence's Indiana home last week, and he has turned those classified records over to the FBI, multiple sources familiar with the matter told CNN.

entries.title: Move could be part of an attempt to break a diplomatic logjam with Germany, which has balked on sending its Leopard 2 tanks
entries.description: The Biden administration is finalizing plans to send US-made Abrams tanks to Ukraine and could make an announcement as soon as this week, according to three US officials familiar with the deliberations.

entries.title: Decisions 'imminent' on Georgia charges in Trump's effort to overturn 2020 election
entries.description: Fulton County District Attorney Fani Willis suggested Tuesday that the special grand jury investigating Donald Trump and his allies' efforts to upend the 2020 election in Georgia has recommended multiple indictments and said that her decision on whether to bring charges is "imminent."

entries.title: Girl calls for help after car rolls over great-grandma
entries.description: Doorbell footage shows the terrifying moment 7-year-old Mariah Galloway called for help after her great-grandma got stuck underneath their rolling SUV. CNN affiliate WXYZ reports.

entries.title: Suspect still at large after overnight shooting in Washington leaves 3 dead
entries.description: At least three people are dead following an overnight shooting in Yakima, Washington, according to Yakima Police Chief Matt Murray.

entries.title: Doomsday Clock updates how close humanity is to total annihilation
entries.description: The Doomsday Clock has been ticking for exactly 75 years. But it's no ordinary clock.

entries.title: This recently identified inflammatory disease may be more common than thought
entries.description: David Adams spent half a decade fighting an illness he couldn't name. He was in and out of the hospital several times per year. His inflamed joints made his hands feel like they had been squeezed into gloves -- and he could no longer play his beloved classical and jazz guitars.

entries.title: Lewis Hamilton details 'traumatizing' racist abuse he says he suffered at school
entries.description: Seven-time Formula One champion Lewis Hamilton has detailed the "traumatizing" racist abuse which he says he suffered at school during an episode of Jess Shetty's 'On Purpose' podcast released on Monday.

entries.title: 9-year-old girl makes rare megalodon find
entries.description: 9-year-old Molly Sampson went fossil hunting in Calvert Beach, Maryland, and discovered a massive tooth from a prehistoric megalodon shark that experts say lived roughly 15 million years ago. CNN affiliate WJLA reports.

entries.title: Mummified 'golden boy' found covered in 49 precious amulets
entries.description: When a teenage boy died 2,300 years ago in Egypt, he was mummified and adorned with 49 protective amulets and a golden mask to guide him in the afterlife.

entries.title: Britain's Princess Eugenie pregnant with second child
entries.description: Britain's Princess Eugenie, niece of King Charles III, is pregnant with her second child, Buckingham Palace said in a statement Tuesday.

entries.title: 'Everything Everywhere All at Once' leads Oscar nominations
Shailene Woodley opens up about Aaron Rodgers relationship
entries.description: Shailene Woodley says she had a tough time filming last year because of what she was going through personally.

entries.title: Trading briefly halted for many New York Stock Exchange-listed stocks
entries.description: Trading for dozens of companies on the New York Stock Exchange was halted Monday morning shortly after the market opened.

entries.title: Oreo's newest cookie is an Oreo stuffed with Oreos
entries.description: In the past, Oreo has partnered with Lady Gaga, Pokémon and Ritz on new limited-time flavors. Now, it's working with ... itself. And Martha Stewart.

entries.title: Amazon launches $5-a-month unlimited prescription plan
entries.description: Amazon is expanding its push into healthcare with a $5 monthly unlimited delivery pass on 60 common generic prescription drugs treating allergies, inflammation, high blood pressure and other conditions.

entries.title: America's biggest banks are taking on Apple Pay and PayPal
entries.description: America's largest banks announced plans Tuesday for an electronic wallet that will take aim at Apple Pay and PayPal.

entries.title: FBI blames North Korea for $100 million crypto heist
entries.description: The FBI on Monday evening blamed North Korean government-linked hackers for stealing $100 million in cryptocurrency last June from a California-based firm.

entries.title: Second mass shooting in California in the last few days
Zelensky shakes up government amid growing corruption scandal
entries.description: A number of senior Ukrainian officials have resigned or been fired by President Volodymyr Zelensky amid a growing corruption scandal linked to the procurement of war-time supplies, in the biggest shakeup of the government since Russia's invasion began.

entries.title: CNN fact-checks McCarthy's 'highly misleading' claims about Pelosi
entries.description: CNN reporter Daniel Dale fact-checks House Speaker Kevin McCarthy's claims about the debt ceiling, funding for the Internal Revenue Service, and the FBI's search of former President Donald Trump's resort and residence in Florida.

entries.title: Europe could dodge a recession. But the UK is in a mess
entries.description: Business activity across the 20 countries that use the euro expanded in January for the first time in six months, according to data published Tuesday, providing fresh evidence that Europe's economy could confound expectations and dodge a recession this year.

entries.title: Ex-FBI official accused of working with Russian oligarch
entries.description: Charles McGonigal, the former head of counterintelligence for the FBI's New York field office, was charged in two separate indictments for allegedly working with Russian oligarch Oleg Deripaska, who was sanctioned for interfering in the 2016 US presidential election, after he retired. McGonigal entered a plea of not guilty via his attorney at an arraignment on charges in connection with violating US sanctions, conspiracy, and money laundering. CNN's Kara Scannell reports.

entries.title: Local lifeguard Luke Shepardson wins iconic big-wave surf event at Hawaii's Waimea Bay
entries.description: A local lifeguard in Hawaii was the surprise winner of the prestigious Eddie Aikau Big Wave Invitational -- dubbed the "Super Bowl of surfing" -- after beating off competition from some of the sport's biggest names.

entries.title: Julian Sands' family praise 'heroic' search efforts to find missing actor
entries.description: The family of missing British actor Julian Sands have thanked "heroic" search teams in California for their efforts to locate him as crews continue to scour the Mt. Baldy area.

entries.title: Bill Gates backs start-up tackling cow burps and farts
entries.description: It turns out burps can be big business. Billionaire Bill Gates has announced an investment in Australian start-up Rumin8, which is developing a seaweed-based feed to reduce the methane emissions cows produce through their burps and, to a lesser extent, farts.

entries.title: Virgin names plane after Queen Elizabeth II
entries.description: The phrase "queen of the skies" has just taken on another meaning.

entries.title: As war continues in Ukraine, Shakhtar Donetsk hopes to send message of hope with 'miracle' season
entries.description: Uprooted from its home in Ukraine's Donbas region in 2014, soccer club Shakhtar Donetsk is accustomed to the change and upheaval brought about by war having played at stadiums around the country for more than a decade.

entries.title: Recently retired Gareth Bale set to compete at PGA Tour's Pebble Beach Pro-Am
entries.description: Just two weeks after retiring from football, Gareth Bale has confirmed he will be back competing with a ball at his feet next month -- albeit a much smaller one.

entries.title: Live Nation exec will face lawmakers about Taylor Swift concert tickets fiasco
entries.description: Lawmakers are set to grill top executives from the event ticketing industry on Tuesday after Ticketmaster's inability to process orders for Taylor Swift's upcoming tour left millions of fans unable to buy tickets or without their ticket even after purchase.

entries.title: Tens of thousands without power in Northeast as another storm threatens the US from New Mexico to Maine
entries.description: Tens of thousands of homes and businesses across multiple states in the Northeast were without power early Tuesday after a winter storm dumped more than a foot of snow across areas from central New York to the Maine-Canada border.

entries.title: WHO urges 'immediate action' after cough syrup deaths
entries.description: The World Health Organization (WHO) has called for "immediate and concerted action" to protect children from contaminated medicines after a spate of child deaths linked to cough syrups last year.

entries.title: Western allies urge Ukraine to shift tactics away from Bakhmut
entries.description: US and Western officials are urging Ukraine to shift its focus from the brutal, months-long fight in the eastern city of Bakhmut and prioritize instead a potential offensive in the south, using a different style of fighting that takes advantage of the billions of dollars in new military hardware recently committed by Western allies, US and Ukrainian officials tell CNN.

entries.title: Victoria Azarenka shines in Melbourne as she sweeps past Jessica Pegula to reach Australian Open semifinals
entries.description: Victoria Azarenka produced a brilliant display of tennis to dispatch world No. 3 Jessica Pegula and reach the Australian Open semifinals.

entries.title: Northern California authorities are investigating a motive after a suspect allegedly killed 7 and critically injured 1
entries.description: Authorities in Northern California are working to determine the motive of a suspect they said killed seven people and injured one in two separate areas of a small coastal city, becoming one of at least three communities in the state to mourn lives lost to mass shootings in three days.

entries.title: Poland requests German approval to send Leopard 2 tanks to Ukraine
entries.description: Poland has formally asked for approval from Germany to transfer German-made Leopard 2 tanks to Ukraine, and Berlin has received the request, the Polish defense minister announced Tuesday.

entries.title: Ghislaine Maxwell claims in jailhouse interview that Prince Andrew photo with Virginia Giuffre is 'fake'
entries.description: Convicted child sex trafficker Ghislaine Maxwell has said a decades-old photograph of Prince Andrew with his sexual abuse accuser Virginia Giuffre is "fake," in a series of interviews from prison.

entries.title: The world's longest flight spent more than two months in the air
entries.description: Late last August, a solar-powered drone called Zephyr almost beat one of aviation's most enduring records.

entries.title: Rui Hachimura acquired by Los Angeles Lakers from the Washington Wizards
entries.description: The Los Angeles Lakers have added Rui Hachimura to their roster after completing a trade for him from the Washington Wizards in exchange for Kendrick Nunn and three second-round picks.

entries.title: 'Disgrace' if Djokovic not allowed to enter US and compete, says Haas
entries.description: Novak Djokovic could end the year as the world's top-ranked player but it would be a "disgrace" if his chances are affected by not being able to compete in the United States due to his unvaccinated status, Indian Wells tournament director Tommy Haas said.

entries.title: 'Westernization is not the answer': Artist Àsìkò explores Yoruba culture through mythology
entries.description: Appreciating cultural heritage and using it to imagine a better future: that's one of the goals of self-taught photographer and visual artist Ade Okelarin.

entries.title: Medics from around the world help Ukraine in Bakhmut
entries.description: CNN's Ben Wedeman speaks with medical workers from around the world who have traveled to Ukraine to help wherever they are needed.

entries.title: Midriff bulge linked to later physical decline, study says
entries.description: If you are a man or woman approaching 50, look down at your middle. If you're like many people, you might have to lean over a bit to see your feet. Yes, it's the dreadful midriff bulge — that expanding waistline that can often creep up on you as you age, much like a receding hairline or extra wrinkles.

entries.title: Rare 17-pound meteorite discovered in Antarctica
entries.description: During a recent excursion to the icy plains of Antarctica, an international team of researchers discovered five new meteorites — including one of the largest ever found on the continent.

entries.title: 'I cried all night': Millions of Chinese lose access to 'World of Warcraft' and other hit games
entries.description: Millions of players in China have lost access to the iconic "World of Warcraft" franchise and other popular video games, as Blizzard Entertainment's servers in the country went offline after two decades.

entries.title: Ben Shelton emerges as US tennis' latest star during dream Australian Open run
entries.description: Rising stars from the United States feature prominently in the men's side of the draw at the Australian Open, making up three of the eight players ithat reached reached the quarterfinals in Melbourne.

entries.title: Russia has sent tens of thousands of new troops to reinforce front lines, US military official says
Bode makes 20th century clothes for 21st century people
entries.description: A few weeks ago, Mick Jagger posted a holiday message to his Instagram feed while wearing a deep red paisley shirt, its pattern whirling with canary yellow and inky black details. The piece had something nostalgically glamourous about it: Decadent yet comfortable, it was as befitting of Jagger's bohemian rockstar aesthetic as it was his timeless presence. "Maybe he got it for Christmas," joked Emily Adams Bode Aujla, creator of the garment and founder of its eponymous label, Bode, over a Zoom call from Paris.

entries.title: Top Ukrainian official steps down
Doja Cat stuns fashion show covered in 30,000 crystals
entries.description: Doja Cat wowed onlookers on Monday as she arrived at Schiaparelli's latest runway show in a dramatic head-to-toe look adorned with red body paint and 30,000 Swarovski crystals.

entries.title: Biden administration raised concerns with Beijing over Chinese companies' non-lethal aid in Russian war effort
entries.description: The Biden administration has recently raised concerns with China about evidence it has suggesting that Chinese companies have sold non-lethal equipment to Russia for use in Ukraine, in an effort to ascertain how much Beijing knows about the transactions, according to two US officials.

entries.title: 'I needed to grab the gun': Man who disarmed Monterey Park shooter hailed as hero
Suspect is in custody following shootings outside San Francisco, just 2 days after a gunman killed at least 11 people in southern California
At least 7 killed in shootings in Half Moon Bay, California
China's northernmost city just saw its coldest day ever
entries.description: Temperatures in China's northernmost city plunged to minus 53°C (minus 63.4 degrees Fahrenheit) -- its coldest ever recorded, meteorologists said.

entries.title: It's 'now or never' to reverse Japan's population crisis, prime minister says
entries.description: Japan's prime minister issued a dire warning about the country's population crisis on Monday, saying it was "on the brink of not being able to maintain social functions" due to the falling birth rate.

entries.title: To eat or stay warm: Afghans are faced with tough choices amid arctic winter
entries.description: Millions of people in Afghanistan are struggling to survive this winter's freezing temperatures, and critics say the Taliban's return to power in 2021 has helped fuel the crisis. CNN's Michael Holmes reports.

entries.title: Surveillance footage shows hero confronting suspected gunman
entries.description: CNN's Anderson Cooper speaks with Brandon Tsay, the man who confronted and disarmed the suspect of the Monterey Park, California, mass shooting that killed 11 people and injured 9 others, about the moment Tsay came face to face with the gunman at a second location nearby.

entries.title: Ukrainian military intelligence document obtained by CNN sets out how effective the group has been around Bakhmut -- and how difficult they are to fight against
entries.description:
• Live updates: Russia sent tens of thousands of new troops to reinforce front lines: US official
• US raised concerns with Beijing over Chinese companies' non-lethal aid in Russia war effort

entries.title: Chinese protester made video warning she could vanish. Then, she disappeared
entries.description: In the weeks following anti-zero Covid protests in Beijing, a protester made a video warning she could vanish. Soon after filming the video, she was arrested. CNN's Selina Wang reports.

entries.title: Tyre Nichols' family attorney says video shows police beating Nichols like a 'human pinata'
entries.description: Attorneys for the family of Tyre Nichols, a Black man who died after a traffic stop in Memphis, Tennessee, said video footage shows the cops' "non-stop beating" of Nichols.

entries.title: See documents that assess Russian private army success
entries.description: CNN has exclusively obtained military documents outlining Kyiv's assessment of the Wagner group, a brutally-effective private Russian army finding success on the battlefield. CNN's Fred Pleitgen has the latest.

entries.title: Suspect in custody after shooting incident with multiple victims in Half Moon Bay, California, police say
entries.description: A suspect is in custody after a shooting incident with multiple victims in the city of Half Moon Bay, California, the San Mateo County Sheriff's Office said.

entries.title: Asia is hurtling toward a tectonic power shift
entries.description: Asia is hurtling toward a tectonic power shift headlined by ever more rapid changes in population growth. The West, especially the United States, better be prepared.

entries.title: Deadly and disposable: Wagner's brutal tactics in Ukraine revealed by intelligence report
